WEBVTT

00:02.928 --> 00:05.306
Barney is crazy if he thinks
this is gonna work.

00:04.263 --> 00:05.222
I think it's
gonna work.

00:05.306 --> 00:06.432
I hope it doesn't work.

00:06.515 --> 00:07.975
Shh. Here he comes.

00:11.687 --> 00:14.398
You there, what's your name?
Excuse me?

00:14.440 --> 00:16.567
Your name, woman,
what's your name?!

00:16.650 --> 00:18.110
Cindy.
I knew it.

00:18.193 --> 00:20.154
You're the Cindy,

00:20.237 --> 00:22.448
the one who can change
everything,

00:22.531 --> 00:25.117
or spell our inevitable doom.

00:25.159 --> 00:27.328
Now listen to me, Cindy.

00:27.411 --> 00:28.746
I am Barney Stinson,

00:28.787 --> 00:32.040
and I am on an urgent mission
from the future.

00:32.082 --> 00:33.250
The future?

00:33.292 --> 00:35.669
The future, and I can
prove it to you.

00:35.711 --> 00:37.921
In exactly four seconds,
the woman at that booth

00:38.005 --> 00:39.715
is going to slap that man.
(clears throat)

00:41.967 --> 00:44.136
Ow! What the hell?

00:44.219 --> 00:45.929
Wow.
In a few minutes,

00:46.013 --> 00:48.599
the young me from your time

00:48.641 --> 00:50.934
is going to come
through that door.

00:51.018 --> 00:52.478
Now, Cindy,

00:52.519 --> 00:57.483
I know this sounds insane,
but in order to save the planet,

00:57.566 --> 01:00.319
you need to sleep with him
tonight.

01:00.402 --> 01:01.445
What? I...

01:01.528 --> 01:04.281
Sleep with Barney Stinson
tonight,

01:04.364 --> 01:05.949
in whatever way he wants it,

01:06.033 --> 01:10.120
or he won't be able to find
the solution to global warming

01:10.162 --> 01:11.955
that saves the human race.

01:12.039 --> 01:13.165
What are you talking about?

01:13.248 --> 01:15.250
I have no time to explain.

01:15.292 --> 01:17.670
I have to get back
to the reality accelerator

01:17.711 --> 01:20.839
before the vortex closes.

01:20.881 --> 01:23.133
Only you can save us, Cindy.

01:23.217 --> 01:25.344
I must away!

01:25.386 --> 01:28.222
Okay, guys, the movers
are coming in 14 hours.

01:28.305 --> 01:30.891
We gotta get back upstairs
and finish packing.

01:30.975 --> 01:32.977
You guys still
aren't finished packing?

01:33.018 --> 01:34.353
How is this taking so long?

01:34.436 --> 01:36.188
Hey, all the great memories
of our 20s

01:36.271 --> 01:37.481
took place in that apartment.

01:37.564 --> 01:39.525
It's not like throwing
stuff in a box.

01:39.608 --> 01:40.526
You start to reminisce.

01:40.609 --> 01:41.944
Not me. The key?

01:41.986 --> 01:43.445
Throw stuff out and never
look back.

01:43.487 --> 01:45.906
I'm moving to Japan.
It took me a half hour to pack.

01:45.948 --> 01:48.409
A half hour?
Well, it would have taken
me 20 minutes,

01:48.450 --> 01:49.868
but a friend called me in tears.

01:49.910 --> 01:52.663
Moving is really
emotional, okay?

01:52.746 --> 01:53.706
It is.

01:53.747 --> 01:55.332
I mean, everything is changing.

01:55.416 --> 01:57.376
I'm gonna be living
in New Jersey with Stella,

01:57.418 --> 01:59.211
you guys will be in
your new place.

01:59.294 --> 02:01.463
You're starting a new job
in Tokyo.

02:01.547 --> 02:03.632
It's the end of an era.

02:03.716 --> 02:06.093
I think we should have a toast,
but not our usual crap.

02:06.176 --> 02:09.054
Hey, uh, Wendy,
your most expensive
bottle of scotch.

02:09.138 --> 02:13.267
That's 50-year-old
Glen McKenna, and it's $2,500.

02:13.350 --> 02:15.644
Excellent. A bottle of that
with beer chasers,

02:15.686 --> 02:17.479
and what do you think,
cancel the scotch?

02:17.521 --> 02:19.440
ALL:
Yeah.

02:21.358 --> 02:22.318
Vodka rocks.

02:22.401 --> 02:24.111
It's not gonna work.

02:24.153 --> 02:27.448
Oh, my God, you're...
Oh, my God!

02:28.615 --> 02:29.616
Can I buy you a drink?

02:31.285 --> 02:33.829
I suppose I have time
for one drink

02:33.912 --> 02:37.583
and 45 minutes to an hour
of some other activity,

02:37.666 --> 02:39.460
but after that,
I have to get back

02:39.543 --> 02:42.254
to a top-secret research project
I'm working on.

02:42.338 --> 02:44.173
Global warming?

02:44.214 --> 02:47.801
My God, how did you know that?

